Interface IgniteCallable<V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Callable<V>, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AtomicIntegerFactoryCallable, ConcurrentHashSetFactoryCallable, ConcurrentMapFactoryCallable, ContentionClosure, IgfsClientAbstractCallable, IgfsClientAffinityCallable, IgfsClientDeleteCallable, IgfsClientExistsCallable, IgfsClientInfoCallable, IgfsClientListFilesCallable, IgfsClientListPathsCallable, IgfsClientMetaIdsForPathCallable, IgfsClientMetaInfoForPathCallable, IgfsClientMetaUnlockCallable, IgfsClientMkdirsCallable, IgfsClientRenameCallable, IgfsClientSetTimesCallable, IgfsClientSizeCallable, IgfsClientSummaryCallable, IgfsClientUpdateCallable, MapFactoryCallable, SetFactoryCallable, ViewCacheClosure

    public interface IgniteCallable<V>
extends Callable<V>, Serializable
    Grid-aware adapter for Callable implementations. It adds Serializable interface to Callable object. Use this class for executing distributed computations on the grid, like in IgniteCompute.call(IgniteCallable) method.

      • Methods inherited from interface java.util.concurrent.Callable
